definitions.definition: A piece of the backbone of an animal, with the adjoining parts, cut for cooking.
( nautical ) A sharp angle in the cross section of a hull .
( aeronautics ) A longitudinal line of sharp change in the cross-section profile of the fuselage or similar body.
( nautical ) A hollowed or bevelled channel in the waterway of a ship's deck.
The edge or rim of a cask , etc., formed by the projecting ends of the staves ; the chamfered end of a stave.
The back of the blade on a scythe .

definitions.definition: A steep-sided ravine leading from the top of a cliff down to the sea.

main_definition: ( Southern England , Vancouver ) A steep-sided ravine leading from the top of a cliff down to the sea.
